The paper deals with the computation of Voronoi diagrams, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry. Therefore, cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses time-space trade-offs, which suggests that it may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper mentions the family of all higher-order Voronoi diagrams, which is related to cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The paper also involves the subdivision of the plane into cells, which is a topic in cs.GR (Computer Graphics). Finally, the paper mentions the use of random access and intermediate data, which suggests that it may belong to cs.SC (Symbolic Computation and Formal Verification).
